Extend the current MVP toward real lesson-based content usage.

Important constraints:
- Do not rewrite the current architecture
- Keep the modular monolith structure
- Reuse the existing domain/application/infrastructure design
- Keep Telegram handlers thin
- Do not add admin bot yet
- Do not add OCR or photo parsing yet
- Focus on lesson-aware vocabulary delivery and structured content packs

Goal of this phase:
Prepare the bot to work with real school materials organized by topics and lessons, using structured importable content.

Please implement the following.

1. Add lesson-aware learner flow
Extend the Telegram learner flow so the user can:
- choose a topic
- then choose either:
  - all words in the topic
  - or a specific lesson within that topic
- then choose training mode
- then start a session

If a topic has no lessons, fall back to topic-only flow cleanly.

2. Introduce lesson repository support if needed
If the current storage layer does not yet expose lesson retrieval cleanly, add the required repository abstraction and in-memory implementation.

At minimum support:
- list lessons by topic
- get lesson by id
- validate lesson belongs to selected topic

3. Make content packs explicit
Introduce a simple structured content format for import-ready vocabulary packs.

Use JSON for this phase.

Example concept:
- topic
- lessons
- vocabulary items

Implement:
- a loader/parser for local JSON content packs
- validation of references (topic ids, lesson ids)
- clear error handling for malformed content

This is not OCR and not admin import yet.
It is a structured content-pack foundation that future manual import or admin tools can use.

4. Provide demo content as JSON
Move or duplicate the current demo data into one or more JSON files under a clear content/demo directory.

Example:
- content/demo/weather.json
- content/demo/school.json

Load them through the new content pack loader instead of hardcoding all demo items in Python lists.

5. Keep application logic clean
Update use cases and bootstrap wiring so lesson-aware flow and JSON-loaded content work without leaking parsing logic into Telegram handlers.

6. Add tests
Add focused tests for:
- listing lessons by topic
- validating topic/lesson combination
- starting a session for a specific lesson
- content pack loading
- malformed JSON/content validation
- fallback when a topic has no lessons

7. Documentation
Update README and ARCHITECTURE:
- explain topic -> lesson -> vocabulary structure
- explain content pack JSON format
- explain how demo content is loaded
- explain how future teacher/admin workflows can prepare JSON packs manually before a full admin bot exists

8. Cleanup if easy
If low-risk and easy, also do the following small cleanup items while working:
- use unique session ids
- fix normalized answer consistency
- make unseen-first logic explicit

Final output:
- summary of changes
- content pack format description
- files changed
- any migration notes from hardcoded demo data
- next recommended step after this phase